    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Speaking of slow-cooked cabbage&#8230; I made Marcella Hazan&#8217;s smothered cabbage and rice soup this weekend, and it is just as delicious as it is ugly &#8211; and it&#8217;s really, really ugly.  Next time you have a cabbage in the fridge, well, I can&#8217;t recommend the soup enough.  SO. GOOD.  (And the ingredients are actually pretty similar to this gratin &#8211; onions instead of scallions, parmesean instead of triple-cream, and a little bit of vinegar, plus rice.)</></>And I will definitely keep this dish in mind next time I crave cabbage (it happens! really!) and I don&#8217;t want to make soup!</p>
