    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Anonymous, I apologize for not replying sooner!  I can&#8217;t say for sure, since I haven&#8217;t tried it, but I do think plain old green cabbage would work for this dish.  It might need to cook a bit longer to reach the same tenderness, but it&#8217;s definitely worth a shot.  And as for the cheese, essentially, you&#8217;re looking for a very rich, very creamy cheese with a smooth, almost buttery flavor.  < HREF="http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2008/09/05/WISL12IJFC.DTL" REL="nofollow">Here<>&#8216;s an article that does a very nice job of describing Delice de Bourgogne, if it helps.</p>
    </div>

